# Trivy vulnerability allowlist  —  IRT-1390
#
# CI (.github/workflows/build-images.yml) gates on FIXABLE HIGH/CRITICAL findings in OS / base-image
# packages only (trivy --ignore-unfixed --pkg-types os) — the layer this repo controls. Full results
# (OS + library, all severities, including unfixed) are uploaded to Security > Code scanning regardless.
#
# Add an entry ONLY to accept a specific OS/base CVE (false positive, not reachable in our config, or
# awaiting a Rocky/DHI erratum). Put the justification + a review date on the comment line ABOVE the
# ID so it is portable across Trivy versions. Keep this list short and re-review dated entries.
#
# Do NOT add library / application-JAR CVEs here — they come from the BridgeLink Core release tarball,
# are already outside the gate scope, and stay visible in the SARIF report; tracked against Core in
# IRT-1396.
#
# Example:
#   # false positive: vulnerable code path not reachable in our config — review by 2026-09-01, dans
#   CVE-2024-12345
#
# (no active entries)
